Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the sliced pepper to the frying pan and stir-fry until just soft,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium, then add the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder). Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Taste the fajita mix and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash
of @water{} if it's little too thick.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your plates and top with the
chicken fajita mix.

Sprinkle over the cheese. Finish with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} - wedges
loaded!

Enjoy!